Description1: Rice, paddy: Rice grain after threshing and winnowing.Also known as rice in the husk and rough rice. Used mainly for human food.
Rice, Husked: Rice grain without hulls or husks. Also known as brown or cargo rice.
Rice, Milled (Husked): White rice milled from imported husked rice. Includes semi-milled, whole-milled and parboiled rice.
Rice, Milled: White rice milled from locally grown paddy. Includes semi-milled, whole-milled and parboiled rice.
Rice, Broken: Residues from the selection of whole-grain, milled rice.
Starch of Rice: See 0023 Rice starch is usually obtained from broken rice. Use primarily in the photographic industry to prepare "matt" paper.
Bran of Rice: A by-product of polishing brown rice, comprising the pericarp, aleurone layer, embryo and some endosperm.
Rice, Gluten: A by-product of the industrial production of starch. Not suitable for food use.
